---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { aboutPageContent, musicPlaylist } from "../config";
import ResumeItem from "../components/ResumeItem.astro";
import SocialLinkBox from "../components/SocialLinkBox.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<Layout seo={aboutPageContent.seo}>
  <section class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h1 class="text-2xl mb-1">About</h1>
    <p class="opacity-60 mb-10 subtitle">{aboutPageContent.subtitle}</p>
    <div class="mb-14">
      <p class="mb-5 sm:text-left">
        Hello üëã, I'm a Software Engineer who adores <span class="gradient-link"
          >JavaScript</span
        > and is passionate about open-source. With a knack for building event-driven
        architecture, I balance code with badminton and find peace in a sip of tea
        and poetry.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-5 sm:text-left">
        My journey started with a simple curiosity ‚Äî how Facebook worked ‚Äî and
        it‚Äôs been an exciting ride ever since. I graduated from <a
          class="gradient-link"
          href="https://vit.ac.in/"
          target="_blank">VIT Vellore</a
        >, worked as a Software Engineer II at <a
          class="gradient-link"
          href="https://www.postman.com/"
          target="_blank">Postman</a
        > where I built products like <a
          href="https://www.postman.com/product/postman-interceptor"
          class="underline-hover"
          target="_blank">Interceptor</a
        > and <a
          href="https://www.postman.com/product/integrations"
          class="underline-hover"
          target="_blank">Integrations</a
        >, and later contributed to scaling neo-banking solutions at <a
          class="gradient-link"
          href="https://www.novo.co/"
          target="_blank">Novo</a
        >.<br /><br />From building core banking systems and ACH rails to
        working on engineering maturity and payments infrastructure, it‚Äôs been a
        deeply rewarding experience at Novo. Discover more about my Postman <a
          href="https://vinitshahdeo.dev/saying-goodbye-to-postman"
          target="_blank"
          class="underline-hover">journey</a
        >, my time at <a
          href="https://vinitshahdeo.dev/celebrating-one-year-at-novo-software-engineer-experience"
          target="_blank"
          class="underline-hover">Novo</a
        >, and valuable <a
          href="https://vinitshahdeo.dev/10-lessons-learned-as-software-engineer-at-postman"
          target="_blank"
          class="underline-hover">lessons</a
        > I've gathered along the way.<br /><br />

        Today, I‚Äôm leading engineering efforts at <a
          href="https://zzazz.com"
          target="_blank"
          class="gradient-link">zzazz</a
        >, an AI startup where we‚Äôre building the world‚Äôs first <i
          >Large Pricing Model</i
        > (LPM) ‚Äî turning online content into valuable, tradable assets. Here, I‚Äôm
        focused on building scalable microservices, designing event-driven platforms,
        and architecting APIs that power AI-driven pricing at internet scale. It‚Äôs
        a thrilling new chapter where deep tech meets real-world impact.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row">
      <Image
        id="about-image-left"
        src={aboutPageContent.about.image_l.url}
        alt={aboutPageContent.about.image_l.alt}
        width={350}
        height={250}
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        quality={100}
        densities={[1.5, 2]}
        class="w-[350px] h-[250px] object-cover rounded-xl sm:-rotate-6 sm:block image-effect"
      />
      <Image
        id="about-image-right"
        src={aboutPageContent.about.image_r.url}
        alt={aboutPageContent.about.image_r.alt}
        width={150}
        height={250}
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        quality={100}
        densities={[1.5, 2]}
        class="hidden w-[150px] h-[250px] object-cover rounded-xl rotate-6 mx-auto sm:ml-auto sm:block image-effect"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="mb-14">
      <p class="mb-5 sm:text-left">
        <strong>Family</strong>, <strong>friends</strong>, and <strong
          >shared laughs</strong
        >? That's where my heart is. Whether it's sharing a cup of tea,
        listening to poetry, or simply enjoying their company, those moments
        mean a lot to me. And, when I'm not in front of my screen, you'll likely
        spot me on the badminton court, rallying shuttlecocks.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-5 sm:text-left">
        <span class="subtitle">I prefer FM Radio over Spotify</span>‚Äîcall me old
        school, but there's something magical about tuning into RJs and their
        spontaneous charm.
        <br /><br />
        <strong>Picture this:</strong> I'm deep into debugging production issues
        while the soothing melody of <a
          href="#"
          id="playSong"
          class="gradient-link">"{musicPlaylist[0].title}"</a
        >
        plays in the background.

        <br /><br />
        <strong
          ><Icon
            name="mdi:music-circle-outline"
            width={25}
            height={25}
            class="icon-inline"
          />Here's a surprise for you</strong
        >‚Äî<span id="enjoySong"></span><span
          class="underline-hover"
          id="clickSong"
          >click here to play
        </span> the current song, and <span
          class="underline-hover"
          id="refreshSong">hit shuffle</span
        > to change tracks.
        <br /><br />

        Offline moments are my luxury, and I treasure them deeply. I find peace
        in late-night strolls and enjoy the simple joys of life.
      </p>
      <audio id="song" src={musicPlaylist[0].url}></audio>
      <p class="mb-5 sm:text-left">
        <a href="https://github.com/vinitshahdeo" target="_blank">
          <img
            src="https://img.shields.io/github/followers/vinitshahdeo.svg?label=Follow%20@vinitshahdeo&style=social"
            alt="GitHub Followers | @vinitshahdeo"
          />
        </a>
      </p>
      <p class="mb-5 sm:text-left">
        <strong>Open Source?</strong> It's a world I'm deeply involved in. I've had
        the privilege of mentoring in <a
          href="https://blog.postman.com/author/vinit-shahdeo/"
          class="underline-hover">GSoC</a
        > at AsyncAPI and Postman. I'm truly honored to be recognized as a <a
          class="gradient-link"
          href="https://stars.github.com/profiles/vinitshahdeo/"
          target="_blank">GitHub Star</a
        >
        for the third time‚Äî2021, 2022, and now in 2025‚Äîrepresenting India among over
        150 million GitHub users and being one of just <strong>70</strong> Stars
        worldwide. I'm always available for a 1:1 chat on <a
          href="https://topmate.io/vinitshahdeo"
          class="underline-hover">Topmate</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
    <script>
      import { musicPlaylist } from "../config";

      let shuffledPlaylist: any[] = [];
      let currentIndex = 0;

      function shuffleArray(array: any[]) {
        for (let i = array.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
          const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
          [array[i], array[j]] = [array[j], array[i]];
        }
        return array;
      }

      shuffledPlaylist = shuffleArray([...musicPlaylist]);

      function randomSong() {
        if (currentIndex >= shuffledPlaylist.length) {
          shuffledPlaylist = shuffleArray([...musicPlaylist]);
          currentIndex = 0;
        }

        const randomSong = shuffledPlaylist[currentIndex];
        currentIndex++;

        const songElement = document.getElementById("song");
        if (songElement instanceof HTMLAudioElement) {
          songElement.src = randomSong.url;
        }

        const playSongElement = document.getElementById("playSong");
        if (playSongElement) {
          playSongElement.textContent = `"${randomSong.title}"`;
        }
      }

      document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
        randomSong();
        initializeEventListeners();
        initializeAudioEvents();
      });

      function updateSongState() {
        const song = document.getElementById("song");
        const icon = document.querySelector(".icon-inline");
        const clickSongElement = document.getElementById("clickSong");
        const enjoySongElement = document.getElementById("enjoySong");

        if (song instanceof HTMLAudioElement) {
          song.volume = 0.3;
          if (song.paused) {
            song.play();
          } else {
            song.pause();
            song.currentTime = 0;
            icon && icon.classList.remove("icon-spin");
            enjoySongElement && (enjoySongElement.textContent = "");
            clickSongElement &&
              (clickSongElement.textContent = "click here to play");
          }
        }
      }

      function initializeEventListeners() {
        document
          .getElementById("playSong")
          ?.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
            event.preventDefault();
            updateSongState();
          });

        document
          .getElementById("refreshSong")
          ?.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
            event.preventDefault();
            randomSong();
            updateSongState();
          });

        document
          .getElementById("clickSong")
          ?.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
            event.preventDefault();
            updateSongState();
          });
      }

      function initializeAudioEvents() {
        const audioElement = document.getElementById("song");
        const songTitleElement = document.getElementById("playSong");
        const icon = document.querySelector(".icon-inline");
        const clickSongElement = document.getElementById("clickSong");
        const enjoySongElement = document.getElementById("enjoySong");
        const leftImageElement = document.getElementById("about-image-left");
        const rightImageElement = document.getElementById("about-image-right");

        if (audioElement && songTitleElement) {
          audioElement.addEventListener("play", () => {
            songTitleElement.classList.add("glowing-animation");
            icon && icon.classList.add("icon-spin");
            leftImageElement &&
              leftImageElement.classList.add("image-music-effect");
            rightImageElement &&
              rightImageElement.classList.add("image-music-effect");
            enjoySongElement &&
              (enjoySongElement.textContent =
                "welcome to my radio station! Scroll further, relax, and enjoy the music! If you're not liking it, ");
            clickSongElement &&
              (clickSongElement.textContent = "click here to stop");
          });

          audioElement.addEventListener("pause", () => {
            songTitleElement.classList.remove("glowing-animation");
            icon && icon.classList.remove("icon-spin");
            leftImageElement &&
              leftImageElement.classList.remove("image-music-effect");
            rightImageElement &&
              rightImageElement.classList.remove("image-music-effect");
            enjoySongElement && (enjoySongElement.textContent = "");
            clickSongElement &&
              (clickSongElement.textContent = "click here to play");
          });

          audioElement.addEventListener("ended", () => {
            songTitleElement.classList.remove("glowing-animation");
            icon && icon.classList.remove("icon-spin");
            enjoySongElement && (enjoySongElement.textContent = "");
            clickSongElement &&
              (clickSongElement.textContent = "click here to play");
          });
        }
      }
    </script>
  </section>

  <section class="my-20 mt-32 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 sm:flex sm:gap-16">
    <h2 class="mb-8 sm:mb-0 opacity-60 navbar">Work</h2>
    <div>
      <div class="mb-6">
        My tech toolbox includes <strong>Node.js</strong>, <strong>Go</strong>, <strong
          >Kafka</strong
        >, <strong>GraphQL</strong>, <strong>REST</strong>, <strong>AWS</strong
        >, and much more ‚Äì but my true love? APIs, of course!
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 group social-bar">
        {aboutPageContent.work.items.map((item) => <ResumeItem {...item} />)}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="mt-32 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 sm:flex sm:gap-16">
    <h2 class="mb-8 sm:mb-0 opacity-60 navbar">Connect</h2>
    <div>
      <div class="mb-6">
        Come find me on ùïè (<a
          href="https://twitter.com/Vinit_Shahdeo"
          target="_blank"
          class="underline-hover">Twitter</a
        >) and <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/vinitshahdeo"
          target="_blank"
          class="underline-hover">LinkedIn</a
        > ‚Äì I'm excited to connect! You can explore my professional side on <a
          href="https://peerlist.io/vinitshahdeo"
          target="_blank"
          class="underline-hover">Peerlist</a
        >. And if you're curious about my thoughts, swing by my blog
        <a class="gradient-link" href="https://vinitshahdeo.dev" target="_blank"
          >vinitshahdeo.dev</a
        >.
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 group social-bar">
        {
          aboutPageContent.connect.links.map((item) => (
            <SocialLinkBox {...item} />
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

